This option allows us to clone the repository in its current (last) state, which will include patchset changes. What exactly happens under the hood (in case of zuul job):
1. zuul clones the PS changes in default_zuul_dir (/home/zuul/src/opendev.org/airship/airshipctl);
2. we define this folder as git repo url to clone from;
3. since we don't perform any checkout - we have latest PS changes cloned to targetPath (not the current master).
You can take a look how does this work here [1] in console logs of script number 23 when I performed some debugging steps to ensure that we cloned repo exactly with current PS changes.

